  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 21 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 2 critical, 13 high, 14 medium, 10 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) and Rome–Fiumicino Leonardo da Vinci (FCO/LIRF); plus 12 other bases. 14 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and fog / freezing fog  — most notably around Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Vilnius (VNO/EYVI) and London Luton (LTN/EGGW). Network hotspots: Copenhagen Kastrup (CPH/EKCH), Malmö Sturup (MMX/ESMS), Valencia (VLC/LEVC), Bordeaux–Mérignac (BOD/LFBD), Hamburg Helmut Schmidt (HAM/EDDH) and 16 others. Primary drivers: snow / blowing snow, low cloud base and thunderstorm / convective risk. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Lyon Saint-Exupéry (LYS/LFLL), Grenoble Alpes Isère (GNB/LFLS) and 9 others.",
